      "id": "25029466991879"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "It is therefore important to determine which entity is most appropriate to take responsibility of different aspects of place. For example, a win-win strategy may be to divide construction and upkeep so that larger scales are taken care of by public-sector institutions, whereas smaller scales are taken care of by more nimble and more local private entities.",
